text: Michele Carey (born Michele Lee Henson, February 26, 1943 â€“ November 21, 2018) was an American actress. She was known for her role as Josephine "Joey" MacDonald in the 1966 movie El Dorado. She appeared in movies in the 1960s and 1970s. She was born in Annapolis, Maryland. She also starred in Live a Little, Love a Little (1968), The Sweet Ride (1968), and Dirty Dingus Magee (1970). Carey died in Newport Beach, California on November 21, 2018 at the age of 75.Fort Collins High School graduate, 'El Dorado' movie star dies: Coloradoan.
